On the 100th anniversary of International Women's Day, the President celebrates the gains made by women and reaffirms support for their rights and opportunities worldwide. The statement emphasizes that when women have access to opportunity, societies are more just and economies prosper. The administration is committed to promoting gender equality and women's empowerment, ending gender-based violence, and increasing women's participation in conflict prevention and resolution. The goal is for women to assume their rightful place as full and equal members of a secure, prosperous, and just world.